.TH "rvt_post_recv" 9 "rvt_post_recv" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rvt_post_recv \- post a receive on a QP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rvt_post_recv
.BI "(struct ib_qp *ibqp "  ","
.BI "const struct ib_recv_wr *wr "  ","
.BI "const struct ib_recv_wr **bad_wr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ibqp" 12
the QP to post the receive on
.IP "wr" 12
the WR to post
.IP "bad_wr" 12
the first bad WR is put here
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This may be called from interrupt context.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success otherwise errno
